OL,6,FIn the consultation document, Ofsted
OL,7,Fsaid: "We will continue to call out
OL,8,Funacceptable practice, as we have
OL,9,Falways done. That is our duty, and
OL,10,Fit's a moral duty as much as a
OL,11,Fprofessional one.
OL,13,F"But these proposals allow us to
OL,14,Fhighlight poor practice with more
OL,15,Fprecision ` pointing laser-like to
OL,16,Fspecific issues, not shining a
OL,17,Ffloodlight on the whole provider."
OL,19,FSir Martyn, chief inspector of Ofsted,
OL,20,Fsaid the death of Mrs Perry has been
OL,21,Fon his mind "ever since it happened".
